module.purpose:
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of 
the data that identify a product.




    Products that this application module can represent, include:



products existing in the real world;

products that may come into existence as a consequence of some realization process. This includes parts and documents;

products that are functions.





			The second edition of this part of ISO 10303 incorporated the modifications to the first edition listed below.



			The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been moved to
			ISO/TS 10303-1016 Product categorization, its use in this part of ISO 10303 removed, and the related mapping
			and MIM EXPRESS declarations moved:



ENTITY Product_category;

ENTITY Product_category_assignment;

FUNCTION types_of_product.
